{
  "texts": [
    "First, Q-learning is a model-free, off-policy RL algorithm that aims to learn the quality of actions.",
    "At each time step, the agent updates the Q-values using the rule:Q(s t, a t) ← Q(s t, a t) + α r t + γ max a ′ Q(s t+1, a ′) -Q(s t, a t) (1)where α is the learning rate and γ is the discount factor.",
    "Second, Dyna-Q is an extension of Q-learning that integrates model-based and model-free learning, using a sample-based environment model to simulate additional experiences.",
    "This hybrid approach allows the agent to learn more efficiently by leveraging real and simulated experiences.",
    "We refer the interested reader to [6] for more details."
  ]
}